Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near coarse red-brown; mixed inclusions, many large. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 27a 13, 71 3 or 96 5. Possibly Rhodian. Compare a piece from Kaunos, B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 352, KA818.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1564)
